---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const serviceSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  "name": "Arena Advertising Revenue Partnership",
  "provider": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Sports Digital Network"
  },
  "description": "Turn your community arena into a revenue generator. SDN installs digital screens, sells ads, and pays you monthly. Zero cost to your facility.",
  "areaServed": {
    "@type": "Country",
    "name": "Canada"
  },
  "serviceType": "Arena Digital Display Partnership"
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Arena Advertising Revenue | Generate Income from Your Facility | SDN"
  description="Turn your community arena into a revenue generator. SDN installs digital screens, sells ads, and pays you monthly. Zero cost to your facility. Learn how."
  canonicalPath="/venues/arenas/"
  schema={serviceSchema}
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <h1>Your arena has thousands of weekly visitors. That's revenue waiting to happen.</h1>
    <p>SDN helps your facility capture the advertising value of your foot traffic — with zero investment or effort from your team.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="intro-section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="lead">Community arenas are some of the most visited public facilities in Canada. A typical multi-pad arena sees 10,000-25,000 visitors per week — hockey families, figure skaters, public skating attendees, event-goers, and league players of all ages.</p>
      <p>Arena advertising revenue through SDN is passive, guaranteed, and requires zero investment or effort from your team. We install digital screens, sell the ad space to national and local brands, manage everything remotely, and send your facility a monthly payment.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="why-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why arenas are premium advertising environments</h2>
      <p>Arenas are ideal for advertisers because of three things that your facility already has:</p>

      <div class="reasons-grid">
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>Dwell time</h3>
          <p>A hockey game lasts 60-90 minutes. A tournament runs all day. Even a quick practice pickup means 30-45 minutes in the building. Visitors aren't passing through — they're staying, which means they see advertising repeatedly during every visit.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>Repeat visitation</h3>
          <p>Hockey families come back 2-4 times per week during the season. Figure skating, public skating, and league play add more repeat visitors. This frequency compounds advertising impressions in a way that billboards and transit ads can't replicate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>Premium demographics</h3>
          <p>Arena visitors skew toward higher-income, family-oriented households. Hockey alone costs $3,000-$7,000+ per year per child — families paying these fees are exactly the audience that national brands and local premium businesses want to reach.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="highlight-text">These factors make your arena's foot traffic valuable to advertisers. SDN makes sure you get paid for it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="install-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What SDN installs in your arena</h2>
      <p>We typically install 2-4 screens per multi-pad facility, positioned in the highest-traffic areas:</p>

      <div class="locations-grid">
        <div class="location-item">
          <strong>Main lobby / entrance</strong>
          <span>every visitor walks past</span>
        </div>
        <div class="location-item">
          <strong>Spectator viewing areas</strong>
          <span>where parents sit during games and practices</span>
        </div>
        <div class="location-item">
          <strong>Hallways between pads</strong>
          <span>high-traffic corridors connecting ice surfaces</span>
        </div>
        <div class="location-item">
          <strong>Scheduling / information areas</strong>
          <span>where players and parents check schedules</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>All screens are 65-inch commercial-grade 4K displays in professional wall mounts. They look sharp, modern, and appropriate for your facility. Several of our arena partners have told us the screens improved the overall look and feel of their building.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What runs on the screens</h2>
      <p>Our screens display a mix of advertising and useful content:</p>

      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-item">
          <strong>Advertising (~50% of screen time)</strong>
          <p>National brand campaigns and local business ads sold and managed entirely by SDN</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-item">
          <strong>Ice schedules and facility information</strong>
          <p>Real-time scheduling data that visitors actually need</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-item">
          <strong>Weather</strong>
          <p>Current conditions and forecasts</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-item">
          <strong>Sports scores</strong>
          <p>NHL, local leagues, and tournament updates</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-item">
          <strong>Community announcements</strong>
          <p>Your facility can feature local event information</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="content-note">The content mix keeps eyes on the screens. Visitors check the schedule, glance at the weather, see the hockey scores — and see your advertisers' messages in between.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="revenue-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Revenue details</h2>

      <div class="revenue-grid">
        <div class="revenue-card">
          <h3>How much can your arena earn?</h3>
          <p>Revenue depends on several factors:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Market size</strong> — arenas in larger metro areas generate more advertising demand</li>
            <li><strong>Visitor traffic</strong> — higher traffic means more impressions, which means more ad revenue</li>
            <li><strong>Number of screens</strong> — more screens in more locations means more inventory to sell</li>
            <li><strong>Number of ice pads</strong> — multi-pad facilities attract more visitors and longer dwell times</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We provide a detailed revenue estimate as part of our partnership proposal, based on your facility's specific data.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="revenue-card">
          <h3>How payment works</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Monthly payments</strong> — predictable, guaranteed revenue every month</li>
            <li><strong>No minimum traffic requirements</strong> — we don't claw back payments if you have a slow month</li>
            <li><strong>Revenue grows</strong> — as we sell more inventory in your facility, your payments can increase</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="zero-effort-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What your arena doesn't have to do</h2>
      <p>This is what makes SDN different from traditional arena advertising programs:</p>

      <div class="zero-grid">
        <div class="zero-item">No selling — SDN's sales team handles all advertiser relationships</div>
        <div class="zero-item">No installation logistics — SDN purchases, ships, and installs all equipment</div>
        <div class="zero-item">No content management — screens are updated remotely by our team</div>
        <div class="zero-item">No maintenance — SDN handles all service and repair at our cost</div>
        <div class="zero-item">No staff time — your arena team doesn't need to do anything beyond providing a wall and an internet connection</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="partners-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Current SDN arena partners</h2>
      <p>SDN operates in partnership with Canada's two largest arena operators:</p>

      <div class="partners-grid">
        <div class="partner-item">
          <strong>Canlan Sports</strong>
          <p>Canada's largest owner/operator of private arena facilities, with locations across Ontario and into Western Canada.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="partner-item">
          <strong>Nustadia Recreation</strong>
          <p>Canada's largest operator of municipal and community arena facilities, managing multi-pad complexes from coast to coast.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="partners-note">We also partner directly with individual municipal facilities and privately operated arenas. If your arena isn't managed by one of these organizations, you can still join the SDN network.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <h2>Apply for an arena partnership</h2>
    <p>If your arena is in a Canadian market and has consistent visitor traffic, we want to hear from you. Fill out our application and we'll send you a preliminary revenue estimate within two business days.</p>
    <a href="/venues/apply/" class="btn-white">Apply now</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .intro-section {
